Looking at lines 140-154 of `finalize.rs`:

```rust
if opts.push {
    // Advance main bookmark to target, then push
    run_jj(
        &["bookmark", "set", "main", "-r", &opts.target, "-R", &repo_str],
        &opts.log,
    )?;
    run_jj(&["git", "push", "-R", &repo_str], &opts.log)?;
}
```

Two problems:

1. **Line 142-153**: It hardcodes `bookmark set main` — so it moved `main` to `@-` (the dev1 commit) even though we'd already set `dev-0.14.0` there
2. **Line 154**: `jj git push` with no `--bookmark` flag pushes **all tracked bookmarks** that have local changes — so it pushed both `main` (just moved) and `dev-0.14.0` (already set by us)

The fix: instead of hardcoding `main`, detect which bookmark(s) already point at `--target` and only push those.
